title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1993-12-18

description: Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Spoonful, Friend Of The Devil, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Tennessee Jed, Easy Answers, Deal Way to Go Home, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Jerry, Phil, Billy and Mickey-> Drums-> Space-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> One More Saturday Night, E: Box Of Rain

reviews.review_text: Fantastic quality audience recording Great sound - even Phil sounds perfect!  This seems almost like a Matrix soundboard, it's that good.  Very solid run of shows to end '93.

  I was unsure on wheter or not this was my source or Dom's Neumann source until I listened to the crowd track at the end with me and Dom talking....but then no more Dom and it's me talking with my other friends who were in a different spot.

Tid bit Was a really good show...people were upbeat and the vibe was through the roof. The band seemed to be elevating to the next level that year... 

Oh how I miss the Coliseum shows... riding BART at midnight after a show was one of the strangest experiences EVER.

Not bad at all... I am definatly not a huge fan of post 1983 Dead but I still listen to a lot of shows from that time and this is one of the best shows of the early 90's. Garcia's guitar is loud and out front, something that starts to dissapear between now and '95. He is using his Cripe and has it set for an almost acoustic/electric guitar sound and that makes for an interesting tone to hear him play with. I love it! The song selection is great hear, TLEO is killer, as is the Playing jams and China/Rider. The band put on a solid show all the way through and that is quite rare for the 90's. I can only think of a handfull of shows from the 90's that are worth owning and this is one of them! Great sounding AUD to boot, nice balanced instruments and levels. Thanks to the tapers!

Thanks! Not having listened to this in about 3 years, I decided to listen once again. Doing things around my house, I didn't shut it off before the "crowd" track at the end. Listening, I hear me talking with one of my  friends who I'll never get the chance to hear from again. I miss you Lynn! Damn if I know what I ever did with my DAT of this show.

Sneaky Great Show Really terrific show highlighted by by Jerry playing the Lightning Bolt Guitar set to be almost acoustic. China Cat through the "Pre-Space Jam" is the highlight, with Uncle John's extraordinary. The jam in FOTD is real good too, as is that in Stella.

Beginning of the end Alas, the post-neuropathy Dead begins. A fantastic first set gives way to a second set where Garcia sounds like he can’t 1) hear himself, 2) remember where the frets are. Every note in Playin’ is missed. Diabetes-related neuropathy was beginning to set in, just as Jer had reached some of the highest levels of playing he’d ever attained in his life and received a new guitar whose onboard buffer played with the one at the end of his pedal chain to produce a timbre like an acoustic guitar but better, and he couldn’t feel his fingers. This would continue throughout 94 & become almost constant in 95. 93 was a fantastic sounding year, & they should have stopped touring after this run. First set is great, but the second is so heartbreaking I can’t listen.
